cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the optimization of downlink multi-antenna systems, which involves the use of information theory, networking, signal processing, and data science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the impact of user selection, spatial correlation, and multi-user diversity, which are relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also mentions multi-stream multiplexing and receive combining, which are related to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and distributed systems (cs.DS).
